	<div id="message857" class="message-text adbayes-content">
		Hello.
<br/><br/>There are 2 different projects: uos and uoslib.
<br/>For Pascal users, please use preferably uos, uoslib is the library version of uos (uos access directly the audio libraries).
<br/>uoslib is a native library that can be used for C, Java, Python, etc.
<br/>But there are less methods than the &quot;pure&quot; uos framework.
<br/><br/>So, please go on this site:
<br/><a href="https://github.com/fredvs/uos" target="_top" rel="nofollow" link="external">https://github.com/fredvs/uos</a><br/><br/>And click on the green button [Code] and &quot;Download zip&quot;.
<br/>I am not sure that OPM has the last release of uos.
<br/><br/>Fre;D

	
	
	
